Another indication of interactions in the early 20th century between Europe and Egypt, including by Americans is at <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9B03E6DF1E31E233A2575AC2A9669D946096D6CF">query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9B03E6DF1E31E233A...</a> , an NYT article from October 29, 1911:
&quot;WAR MAY SPOIL SEASON IN EGYPT; Americans Fear Possible Inconvenience and Will Go to Mediterranean Instead.

LONDON, Oct. 28. -- There are still many Americans staying in London, which is unusually full for this time of year. The hotels continue to do a splendid business, although the weather, which has been damp and foggy, will have the effect of hurrying the departure of those who Winter in warmer climes....&quot;
